"description": "\ud83c\udfa5Authentic Lebanese Food - Huge Mezze: https://youtu.be/lgPf7RTY-yg\n\ud83d\udd14Subscribe http://bit.ly/MarkWiensSubscribe for 2 new videos every week\n\ud83d\udc55T-shirts and caps: https://migrationology.com/store/\n\nWelcome to the Lebanese street food tour of Beirut. It was a full 14 hour day of eating incredibly delicious, and some of the most legendary street food shops in Beirut! #Lebanon #Beirut #LebaneseFood #streetfood\n\nThank you to USAID - My visit to Lebanon was supported by the USAID Lebanon Enterprise Development Project.\n \nFriends in the video:\nThanks to Ibrahim Osta (Director Middle East & North Africa, Chemonics International): https://www.instagram.com/ibrahim_osta/ https://www.facebook.com/ibrahim.osta.35 \nFadi Abu Jaber: https://www.instagram.com/jordanality/\nKamel: https://www.instagram.com/feryal.boutique/\n\nHere are the restaurants and stalls we ate at during this Lebanese street food tour:\n\nHajj Nasr Sandwich Shop - By 6 am, when Beirut is about to wake up, Hajj Nasr is getting ready to close. We arrived at 5 am to make sure he still had food. The tebleh nayyeh - Raw meat, garlic, tomatoes, mint, and the soujouk - soujouk sausage, garlic, tomatoes, pickles - sandwiches were incredible. Total price - 15,000 LBP ($9.95)\n\nFaysal Snack (https://goo.gl/maps/FidmkbQNjBDqUBxn9) - Great Lebanese pastries and breads. We ordered the halloumi loaf, plus some Man'ousheh (Manakish) topped with za'atar, and some spinach pastries. 19,000 LBP ($12.60) - Total price for everything\n\nHanna Mitri (https://goo.gl/maps/iBTb64g5qprq3z6s9) - If you mention ice cream in Beirut, this is the place that everyone knows and everyone loves - it\u2019s a Lebanese ice cream icon, and it\u2019s uniquely delicious from any other ice cream I\u2019ve had in the world. It\u2019s special without a doubt.\n\nAl Soussi Restaurant (https://goo.gl/maps/acSHkHamuvaD1vNFA) - This is one of the most famous restaurants in Beirut, especially for breakfast. Their fattey and hummus is good, but nothing compares to their awarma and eggs.\n\nFalafel Tabbara (https://goo.gl/maps/3bfTAT7Hitxmz3LK6) - Unique falafel - His falafel are made purely with fava beans, in a donut shape. 2,500 LBP ($1.66) - Price per sandwich\n\nIchkhanian Bakery (https://goo.gl/maps/bppJWMhBYMAfviJd6) - This is a legendary Armenian Lebanese bakery that specializes in Lahmajoun (Lahmacun) - Thin dough topped with minced meat. 9,000 LBP ($5.97) - Total price for everything\n\nLamb head - 15,000 LBP ($9.95) - Total price for lamb head\n\nMakari Sweets Shop - Home of mfata\u2019a, which is a unique and rare to find nowadays rice pudding, tahini, and turmeric pudding.\n\nRestaurant Joseph (https://goo.gl/maps/6PDTiaayZ7dPD3px6) - If you\u2019re looking for the best Lebanese shawarma in Beirut, this is the spot. The chicken was good, but the beef was the best. 6,000 LBP ($3.98) - Price per sandwich\n\nL'abeille D'or (https://goo.gl/maps/SKweQNzEpERr3mVb9) - Finally, we ended this ultimate 14 hour street food tour in Beirut, Lebanon at a very non street food, gourmet Lebanese sweets shop to eat Kanafeh. But the Lebanese way, in a bun.\n\nIt was an amazing day of Lebanese food, culture, and people, in Beirut, Lebanon!\n\n\ud83c\udfb5MUSIC: \n\u201cLondon Beat\u201d\nhttps://www.audionetwork.com/\n\n\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014\n\n\ud83c\udf4cBanana Chips are available now worldwide!!\nhttps://m.me/BananaJoe?ref=MarkWiens\n\n\ud83d\udc55Get t-shirts and caps:\nhttps://migrationology.com/store/\n\n\ud83d\udcf7Camera gear I use:\nhttps://kit.com/markwiens/camera-video-gear\n\n\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014\n\n\ud83d\udcf1FOLLOW:\nInstagram: https://instagram.com/migrationology\nFacebook: https://www.facebook.com/migrationology", "thumbnails": {"default": {"url": "https://i.ytimg.com/vi/wSwpV85OXNs/default.jpg", "width": 120, "height": 90}, "medium": {"url": "https://i.ytimg.com/vi/wSwpV85OXNs/mqdefault.jpg", "width": 320, "height": 180}, "high": {"url": "https://i.ytimg.com/vi/wSwpV85OXNs/hqdefault.jpg", "width": 480, "height": 360}, "standard": {"url": "https://i.ytimg.com/vi/wSwpV85OXNs/sddefault.jpg", "width": 640, "height": 480}, "maxres": {"url": "https://i.ytimg.com/vi/wSwpV85OXNs/maxresdefault.jpg", "width": 1280, "height": 720}}, "channelTitle": "Mark Wiens", "tags": ["Lebanese food", "street food", "street food Lebanon", "street food Beirut", "Beirut best food", "street food tour", "street food tour Lebanon", "Mark Wiens", "food vlog", "food blog", "food videos", "food travel", "shawarma", "Kanafeh", "Makari Sweets Shop", "lamb", "Lahmajoun", "Ichkhanian Bakery", "falafel", "Al Soussi Restaurant", "best restaurants Beirut"], "categoryId": "19", "liveBroadcastContent": "none", "defaultLanguage": "en", "localized": {"title": "Street Food in Lebanon - We arrived at 5 am to make sure he still had food. The tebleh nayyeh - Raw meat, garlic, tomatoes, mint, and the soujouk - soujouk sausage, garlic, tomatoes, pickles - sandwiches were incredible. We ordered the halloumi loaf, plus some Man'ousheh (Manakish) topped with za'atar, and some spinach pastries. 19,000 LBP ($12.60) - Total price for everything\n\nHanna Mitri (https://goo.gl/maps/iBTb64g5qprq3z6s9) - If you mention ice cream in Beirut, this is the place that everyone knows and everyone loves - it\u2019s a Lebanese ice cream icon, and it\u2019s uniquely delicious from any other ice cream I\u2019ve had in the world. It\u2019s special without a doubt.\n\nAl Soussi Restaurant (https://goo.gl/maps/acSHkHamuvaD1vNFA) - This is one of the most famous restaurants in Beirut, especially for breakfast. Their fattey and hummus is good, but nothing compares to their awarma and eggs.\n\nFalafel Tabbara (https://goo.gl/maps/3bfTAT7Hitxmz3LK6) - Unique falafel - His falafel are made purely with fava beans, in a donut shape. 2,500 LBP ($1.66) - Price per sandwich\n\nIchkhanian Bakery (https://goo.gl/maps/bppJWMhBYMAfviJd6) - This is a legendary Armenian Lebanese bakery that specializes in Lahmajoun (Lahmacun) - Thin dough topped with minced meat. 9,000 LBP ($5.97) - Total price for everything\n\nLamb head - 15,000 LBP ($9.95) - Total price for lamb head\n\nMakari Sweets Shop - Home of mfata\u2019a, which is a unique and rare to find nowadays rice pudding, tahini, and turmeric pudding.\n\nRestaurant Joseph (https://goo.gl/maps/6PDTiaayZ7dPD3px6) - If you\u2019re looking for the best Lebanese shawarma in Beirut, this is the spot. The chicken was good, but the beef was the best. 6,000 LBP ($3.98) - Price per sandwich\n\nL'abeille D'or (https://goo.gl/maps/SKweQNzEpERr3mVb9) - Finally, we ended this ultimate 14 hour street food tour in Beirut, Lebanon at a very non street food, gourmet Lebanese sweets shop to eat Kanafeh. But the Lebanese way, in a bun.\n\nIt was an amazing day of Lebanese food, culture, and people, in Beirut, Lebanon!\n\n\ud83c\udfb5MUSIC: \n\u201cLondon Beat\u201d\nhttps://www.audionetwork.com/\n\n\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014\n\n\ud83c\udf4cBanana Chips are available now worldwide!!\nhttps://m.me/BananaJoe?ref=MarkWiens\n\n\ud83d\udc55Get t-shirts and caps:\nhttps://migrationology.com/store/\n\n\ud83d\udcf7Camera gear I use:\nhttps://kit.com/markwiens/camera-video-gear\n\n\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014\n\n\ud83d\udcf1FOLLOW:\nInstagram: https://instagram.com/migrationology\nFacebook: https://www.facebook.com/migrationology"}, "defaultAudioLanguage": "en"}, "contentDetails": {"duration": "PT45M58S", "dimension": "2d", "definition": "hd", "caption": "false", "licensedContent": true, "contentRating": {}, "projection": "rectangular"}, "statistics": {"viewCount": "5569655", "likeCount": "65430", "dislikeCount": "2647", "favoriteCount": "0", "commentCount": "6437"}, "recordingDetails": {"locationDescription": "Beirut", "location": {"latitude": 33.8937913, "longitude": 35.5017767, "altitude": 0}}}, {"kind": "youtube#video", "etag": "LG8QUy98pAldqFVpJ7Mvx9EYlYc", "id": "tu-bgIg-Luo", "snippet": {"publishedAt": "2019-11-15T16:00:10Z", "channelId": "UC8NGHNySIDxX2RD80PRl7aQ", "title": "Aram MP3 - In this video we went on an ultimate street food tour of Tripoli, discovered some of the unique local foods, including the most amazing stretchy CHEESE WATERFALL dessert I\u2019ve ever seen - it was an amazing day in Lebanon. #Lebanon #Tripoli #LebaneseFood #streetfood\n\nHere\u2019s everything we did on this Lebanese street food tour in Tripoli:\n\nKaake Traboulsi - The breakfast staple in Tripoli is a type of bread called kaake traboulsi, filled with cheese and sumac and grilled. 1,000 LBP ($0.66) - Price for 1\n\nRestaurant of Happiness - Really that\u2019s the name! - This bakery was incredible, so much action and energy, and the baked goods were delicious. 21,000 LBP ($13.93) - Price for everything\n\nThe Great Mosque of Tripoli - Mamluk Mosque completed in 1314 - We then did some sightseeing in the ancient city of Tripoli, the Great Mosque and to the Citadel of Raymond de Saint-Gilles which was built during the Crusades. The views of the city were fantastic and gave a nice perspective of the city.\n\nMoghrabieh - Couscous from Morocco - This is a very interesting food in Tripoli, with influence of Morocco, but big balls of couscous wrapped in a sandwich. But the best thing about this place was the amazing stretchy cheese dessert. 1,500 LBP ($1.00) - Price per sandwich\n\nAl-Abd Hammam - One of the highlights of the day was visiting the old Hamam, a Turkish bath built in the 17th Century during the Ottoman period. It was great to take a rest and drink a coffee in the hammam.\n\nBayt El Falafel - Falafel Restaurant - 1,500 LBP ($1.00) - Price per sandwich\n\nKalasina Chicken (https://goo.gl/maps/KwQw59L9kZoi4G9v8) - Grilled and rotisserie chicken, which is a popular food in Tripoli, and this place was delicious. Their garlic was amazing. 20,000 LBP ($13.27) - Price for everything\n\nThe Sailor Woman - Finally, to end this Lebanese street food tour in Tripoli, we went to The Sailor Woman to eat a mix of seafood sandwiches, but mainly samke harra, a spiced fish with tahini.\n\nIt was an amazing day in Tripoli, Lebanon and I loved the food and entire energy of the city.\n\nThank you to USAID - But along with the ruins, Baalbek is known for its unique bakery foods and lots of grilled meat. This turned out to be one of my favorite dates in Lebanon for the mix of food, culture, and history. #Baalbek #Lebanon #LebaneseFood\n\nLaiterie Massabki - On the drive from Beirut to Baalbek, we took the highway that goes from Beirut to Damascus, Syria, and Kamel mentioned that almost everyone who makes the drive stops for some cheese sandwiches a long the way, so we had to stop. They turned out to be incredibly delicious, well worth a stop. Total price - 26,000 LBP ($17.25)\n\nSfiha Baalbakiyye - One of the highlights of the day and of my trip to Lebanon was going to the butchery to order fresh kebabs. At the butchery they also ground fresh meat, mixed it with herbs and spices, and then we took it to the bakery across the street to make Sfiha Baalbakiyye. The bakery skills they had were super human! The kebabs and kofta were stunning as well. 65,000 LBP ($43.12) - Price for all meat and pastries \n\nPalmyra Hotel - Kamel knows the manager of the classic Palmyra Hotel, which has been in continual operation for the last 140 years. After walking around the hotel for a bit, we had a Baalbek style food lunch in their courtyard. Food was delicious, fresh, and different tasting from a lot of the Lebanese food I had tried so far. After lunch we went to a very kind womans home to see the local Baalbek cheese and have a coffee as well.\n\nBaalbek Ruins - And to finish off this food and attractions tour of Baalbek, we visited the famous ruins. Lebanese food! For a long long time now, I\u2019ve been a huge fan of Lebanese food. Even as a kid, I would go out to eat Lebanese food with my parents, and we\u2019d some of the most common dishes like hummus, tabbouleh, baba ghanoush and shish taouk. So already with a love for Lebanese cuisine, I was thrilled to be in Beirut, Lebanon, for the first time, to try the real food!\n\nWhat is Mezze? - Mezze is an entire culture of eating small dishes served as appetizers and salads. Along with a full mezze spread, it\u2019s common to drink arak, a traditional Levantine spirit made from grapes and aniseed.\n\nAbou Hassan Restaurant (https://goo.gl/maps/X9PMsa54MHgekLrg9) - Maya brought us to Abou Hassan, a well known mezze and Lebanese food restaurant in Beirut. I loved it from the moment I walked in and saw all the different mezze appetizers and salads lined up and waiting to be ordered. It was without a doubt a festival of foods, flavors, colors, a true taste of Lebanese eating culture.\nHere are a few of the dishes we ordered:\nTabbouleh - Salad of parsley, bulgar, tomatoes, onions, lemon\nWarak Enab - Stuffed grape leaves\nLebanese Toum - King of dips, pure garlic blended with vegetable oil\nShanklish - Aged Levantine cheese\nLamb Brains - Saut\u00e9ed with garlic sauce\nTagine - Tahini (sesame paste), roasted nuts\nChicken Hearts - Caramelised in pomegranate molasses\n\nAl Halabi Restaurant (https://goo.gl/maps/rkYpWgqZSsJFqPWr7) - Next, my friend Kamel () brought us to Al Halabi Restaurant, an iconic restaurant in Beirut, known for mezze and especially for the Lebanese raw meat platter. Raw meat is commonly eaten in Lebanon, and it\u2019s a delicacy and it\u2019s incredibly delicious. We had raw lamb fat, meat of various textures, kibbeh nayyeh, and raw liver. Additionally, after another spectacular Lebanese meal, we were ushered to another table that was filled with dessert - a bounty of never ending fruit and sweet desserts.\n\nThank you again to USAID Lebanon Enterprise Development Project for supporting my trip to Lebanon.\n\n\ud83c\udfb5MUSIC: \n\u201cLike a Ricochet\u201d\nhttps://goo.gl/HwVjdo and https://www.audionetwork.com/\n\n\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014\n\n\ud83c\udf4cBanana Chips are available now worldwide!!\nhttps://m.me/BananaJoe?ref=MarkWiens\n\n\ud83d\udc55Get t-shirts and caps:\nhttps://migrationology.com/store/\n\n\ud83d\udcf7Camera gear I use:\nhttps://kit.com/markwiens/camera-video-gear\n\n\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014\n\n\ud83d\udcf1FOLLOW:\nInstagram: https://instagram.com/migrationology\nFacebook: https://www.facebook.com/migrationology", "thumbnails": {"default": {"url": "https://i.ytimg.com/vi/lgPf7RTY-yg/default.jpg", "width": 120, "height": 90}, "medium": {"url": "https://i.ytimg.com/vi/lgPf7RTY-yg/mqdefault.jpg", "width": 320, "height": 180}, "high": {"url": "https://i.ytimg.com/vi/lgPf7RTY-yg/hqdefault.jpg", "width": 480, "height": 360}, "standard": {"url": "https://i.ytimg.com/vi/lgPf7RTY-yg/sddefault.jpg", "width": 640, "height": 480}, "maxres": {"url": "https://i.ytimg.com/vi/lgPf7RTY-yg/maxresdefault.jpg", "width": 1280, "height": 720}}, "channelTitle": "Mark Wiens", "tags": ["Lebanon", "Lebanese food", "Beirut", "best food Beirut", "best Lebanese food", "Middle Eastern Food", "Lebanese cuisine", "kibbeh", "mezze", "Lebanese mezze", "Mark Wiens", "best restaurants in Beirut", "Al Halabi Restaurant", "food videos", "kibbeh nayyeh", "things to do in beirut", "things to do in Lebanon"], "categoryId": "19", "liveBroadcastContent": "none", "defaultLanguage": "en", "localized": {"title": "Authentic Lebanese Food - Along with a full mezze spread, it\u2019s common to drink arak, a traditional Levantine spirit made from grapes and aniseed.\n\nAbou Hassan Restaurant (https://goo.gl/maps/X9PMsa54MHgekLrg9) - Maya brought us to Abou Hassan, a well known mezze and Lebanese food restaurant in Beirut. I loved it from the moment I walked in and saw all the different mezze appetizers and salads lined up and waiting to be ordered. It was without a doubt a festival of foods, flavors, colors, a true taste of Lebanese eating culture.\nHere are a few of the dishes we ordered:\nTabbouleh - Salad of parsley, bulgar, tomatoes, onions, lemon\nWarak Enab - Stuffed grape leaves\nLebanese Toum - King of dips, pure garlic blended with vegetable oil\nShanklish - Aged Levantine cheese\nLamb Brains - Saut\u00e9ed with garlic sauce\nTagine - Tahini (sesame paste), roasted nuts\nChicken Hearts - Caramelised in pomegranate molasses\n\nAl Halabi Restaurant (https://goo.gl/maps/rkYpWgqZSsJFqPWr7) - Next, my friend Kamel () brought us to Al Halabi Restaurant, an iconic restaurant in Beirut, known for mezze and especially for the Lebanese raw meat platter. | Amazing Mediterranean Food!", "description": "\ud83c\udfa5Ultimate Street Food Tour in Beirut: https://youtu.be/wSwpV85OXNs\n\ud83d\udc55T-shirts and caps: https://migrationology.com/store/\n\ud83c\udf4cMark Wiens Banana Chips - Worldwide Shipping Available Now: https://m.me/BananaJoe?ref=MarkWiens\n\nTYRE, LEBANON - Tyre is an ancient coastal city of Lebanon, that dates back to 2750 BC as a Phoenician City. It\u2019s a fishing city, and so we set out to go on a fishing experience and eat local fish and hummus with a fisherman. Even though our catch was small, it was a hugely learning experience. #Lebanon #Tyre #fishing\n\nThank you to USAID - My visit to Lebanon was supported by the USAID Lebanon Enterprise Development Project. Thanks to Ibrahim Osta (Director Middle East & North Africa, Chemonics International): https://www.instagram.com/ibrahim_osta/ https://www.facebook.com/ibrahim.osta.35 \n\nFriends in the video:\nThank you to Maya\nFadi Abu Jaber: https://www.instagram.com/jordanality/\nKamel: https://www.instagram.com/feryal.boutique/\n\nMahfouz Sandwich Shop - The day before going fishing, we met up with the fisherman and ate some sandwiches at the legendary Mahfouz sandwich stop. Some people drive all the way from Beirut just to eat these sandwiches. The meat combinations and sweet pepper is what made them so good to me.\n\nFishing in Tyre - We woke up about 4 am and set off to go fishing. The fishermen had already been out for a while in the night, and they had a small catch. We set off, and cast the nets a few times, but didn\u2019t have much luck. We did catch a few small fish, but nothing much. Captain said it was the slow part of the season, so fishing wasn\u2019t very good.\n\nSo we ended up buying a bigger fish from the market, though still local fish from the Mediterranean Sea. We bought a pigfish, which we brought to the bakery to bake.\n\nBaroud Restaurant - As the fish was baking we walked over to Baroud restaurant to order some hummus as Captain said he always eats hummus with fish. We also had to quickly try their ful, which was excellent. I still think the best ful though is in Saida.\n\nAfter the fish was finished baking, we brought the fish and the hummus to the local fisherman canteen at the port, and feasted. The fish was incredible, so flaky and firm, and I think it was my first time to ever really eat fish and hummus as the main combination of the meal - and it works so well!\n\nA breathtaking experience, and just a slight glimpse into the life of a fisher life in Tyre, Lebanon.\n\n\ud83c\udfb5MUSIC: \n\u201cUltimate Hope\u201d It\u2019s a fishing city, and so we set out to go on a fishing experience and eat local fish and hummus with a fisherman. Even though our catch was small, it was a hugely learning experience. #Lebanon #Tyre #fishing\n\nThank you to USAID - My visit to Lebanon was supported by the USAID Lebanon Enterprise Development Project. Thanks to Ibrahim Osta (Director Middle East & North Africa, Chemonics International): https://www.instagram.com/ibrahim_osta/ https://www.facebook.com/ibrahim.osta.35 \n\nFriends in the video:\nThank you to Maya\nFadi Abu Jaber: https://www.instagram.com/jordanality/\nKamel: https://www.instagram.com/feryal.boutique/\n\nMahfouz Sandwich Shop - The day before going fishing, we met up with the fisherman and ate some sandwiches at the legendary Mahfouz sandwich stop. Some people drive all the way from Beirut just to eat these sandwiches. The meat combinations and sweet pepper is what made them so good to me.\n\nFishing in Tyre - We woke up about 4 am and set off to go fishing. The fishermen had already been out for a while in the night, and they had a small catch. We set off, and cast the nets a few times, but didn\u2019t have much luck. We did catch a few small fish, but nothing much. Captain said it was the slow part of the season, so fishing wasn\u2019t very good.\n\nSo we ended up buying a bigger fish from the market, though still local fish from the Mediterranean Sea. We bought a pigfish, which we brought to the bakery to bake.\n\nBaroud Restaurant - As the fish was baking we walked over to Baroud restaurant to order some hummus as Captain said he always eats hummus with fish. We also had to quickly try their ful, which was excellent. I still think the best ful though is in Saida.\n\nAfter the fish was finished baking, we brought the fish and the hummus to the local fisherman canteen at the port, and feasted. The fish was incredible, so flaky and firm, and I think it was my first time to ever really eat fish and hummus as the main combination of the meal - and it works so well!\n\nA breathtaking experience, and just a slight glimpse into the life of a fisher life in Tyre, Lebanon.\n\n\ud83c\udfb5MUSIC: \n\u201cUltimate Hope\u201d \u201cCadiz\u201d\nhttps://www.audionetwork.com/\n\n\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014\n\n\ud83c\udf4cBanana Chips are available now worldwide!!\nhttps://m.me/BananaJoe?ref=MarkWiens\n\n\ud83d\udc55Get t-shirts and caps:\nhttps://migrationology.com/store/\n\n\ud83d\udcf7Camera gear I use:\nhttps://kit.com/markwiens/camera-video-gear\n\n\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014\n\n\ud83d\udcf1FOLLOW:\nInstagram: https://instagram.com/migrationology\nFacebook: https://www.facebook.com/migrationology"}, "defaultAudioLanguage": "en"}, "contentDetails": {"duration": "PT28M13S", "dimension": "2d", "definition": "hd", "caption": "true", "licensedContent": true, "contentRating": {}, "projection": "rectangular"}, "statistics": {"viewCount": "1636260", "likeCount": "26460", "dislikeCount": "1098", "favoriteCount": "0", "commentCount": "1698"}, "recordingDetails": {"locationDescription": "Tyre", "location": {"latitude": 33.2704888, "longitude": 35.2037641, "altitude": 0}}}, {"kind": "youtube#video", "etag": "L_evX0Qpnhsd9ZRzAORd831_nho", "id": "qmvo1VmQ1EA", "snippet": {"publishedAt": "2019-08-09T16:58:16Z", "channelId": "UC1SawInmaC5j-QOPyOCN_Bg", "title": "Shabjdeed - SINDIBAD (Prod. And lastly, we walked along the gorgeous Corniche Beirut waterfront.\n\nHotel Albergo (https://goo.gl/maps/5ndJzdavkRBnV5oQ9) - We were invited for a rooftop sunset drink at the top of Hotel Albergo, a beautiful historical hotel in Beirut. The view was outstanding, and a perfect was to finish a day in Beirut.\n\nHope you enjoyed this simple Beirut travel guide!\n\n\ud83c\udfb5MUSIC: Meyvelerini Meryem\u2019in deposunda saklad\u0131\u011f\u0131 i\u00e7in Nurcan, Mustafa Ali\u2019ye \u00e7\u0131k\u0131\u015f\u0131r ve bilmedi\u011fi i\u015fi yapmamas\u0131n\u0131 ister. Mustafa Ali de Nurcan\u2019\u0131n bilmeden ba\u015flad\u0131\u011f\u0131 tatl\u0131c\u0131l\u0131\u011f\u0131na dem vurunca aralar\u0131nda bir iddiala\u015fma ortaya \u00e7\u0131kar. Mustafa Ali, kuru meyve i\u015fine \u015fimdi daha bir d\u00f6rt elle sar\u0131l\u0131p kurutma cihazlar\u0131 alacakken \u00f6n\u00fcne ge\u00e7mi\u015ften gelen bir engel \u00e7\u0131kar. Bu engeli a\u015fmak zorundad\u0131r. Mustafa Ali i\u015flerini geli\u015ftirip \u0130stanbul\u2019a d\u00f6nmeyi mi d\u00fc\u015f\u00fcn\u00fcyordur?\n\nDi\u011fer yandan Dudu, \u015eakir\u2019in \u00fczerine fazla gitti\u011fini kabul edip \u015eakir\u2019in g\u00f6nl\u00fcn\u00fc almak i\u00e7in t\u00fcrl\u00fc yollar dener. Fakat bu g\u00f6n\u00fcl alma i\u015fi hi\u00e7 de kolay olmayacakt\u0131r. Dudu\u2019ya \u015eakir\u2019le bar\u0131\u015fs\u0131n diye hi\u00e7 beklemedi\u011fi bir ki\u015fi yard\u0131m edecektir.\n\nMeryem ve Ercan cephesinde ise i\u015fler Behice geldi\u011finden beri daha bir kar\u0131\u015f\u0131kt\u0131r. Meryem, Ercan\u2019a bir g\u00fczellik yapmaya karar verir fakat \u00f6ncesinde Ercan\u2019\u0131 yo\u011furthaneye bek\u00e7i yaparak s\u0131namak ister. The base is grilled and pureed eggplants mixed with yogurt. Top of that is ground meat cooked in tomato sauce.  Originally finally chopped cubed meat is used (mostly lamb meat) with sheep tail fat. This is one of our favourite cities and we've spent 2 months eating our way around Istanbul to create this series. This 4 part series is about showing you the best Istanbul street food and hunting down local food and heritage Turkish shops and restaurants which are Istanbul icons. Watch our previous Istanbul series here: https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLg-t2nQXCum5H6OdIDcl7QRM48xidTQPS\n\nThis is our fourth Istanbul food video and it's based in Kadikoy on the Asian side of Istanbul- where we've been staying for the past couple of months. We start with muhlama a speciality from the Black Sea region- it's basically Turkish cheese fondue! Made up of local cheese, cornmeal and a tonne of butter and served with bread- a delicious, cheesy breakfast! \n\nNext up we hunt down one of Turkey's most unusual street foods- it's from Adana and isn't too common in Istanbul- it's called \u015e\u0131rdan and is a sheep's intestine which is stuffed with rice and then sewn up and cooked slowly in broth before being sprinkled with chilli and cumin to serve. It's the most unusual looking street food we have ever seen- really phallic!\n\nOnwards for a giant kebab feast with our friends Josh and Ashley from The Way Away (check out their channel here: https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCxn5zB_-HOiBGzdMSRiq_HA).\nKebab is a general term for any type of meat which is fashioned onto a skewer and then roasted or grilled. At Aboov's we eat Adana kebab (spicy minced lamb), tavuk kanat (chicken wings) and lamb \u015fi\u015f kebab (cubes of lamb). Kebab are usually served with lavash (flatbread), ezme a Turkish salad of tomatoes, parsley, onion and pomegranate molasses, onions and parsley tossed in sumac and pickles. We wash it down with a cup of fresh ayran- a salty, thin yoghurt drink. \n\nWe hope you enjoyed this Istanbul food tour! 293\nhttps://goo.gl/maps/2C5Aq5t888k1S2ZP6\n\nTo the sound of chirping birds, I walked down the stairs to Krikor. Calmness takes over the mountain, the wind caresses the trees and Krikor sitting in his little hole in the wall under the low ceiling takes care of his oven a log at a time. Even the oven is special, created to host gas on one side and wood on the other giving off a smooth flame that cooks inside out while offering a crunchy envelope. Fifty-four long years of experience where Krikor mastered the art of breakfast. Fifty-four years of artisanal work to create a rare jewel not many know how to master.\n\nAt 3am, the dough is prepared and ready to enter the oven as and when the client asks for it. A layer of kashkaval cheese lies under the Awarma meat. Beef meets with lamb fat. Kashkawan, mozzarella, and local cheese all together freshly shredded, two eggs and more cheese\u2026 Baked for seven long minutes on a low fire before taking it out of the oven to add the final touches of taste and shine - that's the fat. A bomb and surely not your average sandwich. This is breakfast, lunch, and dinner combined. A firm and lightly chewy dough with a crunchy bottom topped with a moist and melting egg and cheese, shining beautifully, a heavenly explosion inside your mouth to activate all your senses in an instant. This is one of our favourite cities and we've spent 2 months eating our way around Istanbul to create this series. This 4 part series is about showing you local Turkish foods and hunting down the more unusual but tasty Istanbul street food that you might not have seen before. Watch our previous Istanbul series here: https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLg-t2nQXCum5H6OdIDcl7QRM48xidTQPS\n\nThis is our second Istanbul food video. We start with d\u00f6ner kebab, the king of Istanbul street food. Next up we head into the laneways of the old town and eat k\u00f6fte (meatballs)- this place has been around since 1960 and the atmosphere is half the pleasure as you're surrounded by the buzz of the city as you eat on the street. Onwards to one of the city's quirkiest phenomena- a gazoz shop. Gazoz are Turkish soft drinks. There has been a revival of these nostalgic drinks which date back to the early 1900s when most towns and cities had their own local gazoz. We sample a few flavoured gazoz before heading for another sweet treat called bici bici. Bici bici is from the southern city of Adana where it's a popular street food in the summertime. Finally we head for one of our favourite Turkish street foods- kelle s\u00f6\u011f\u00fc\u015f or cold boiled sheep's head. Muammer Usta has been serving this dish for over 40 years from his small street card. Sliced sheep's head, onions, parsley and chilli makes for a delicious snack. A must eat! \n\nWe hope you enjoyed this Istanbul street food tour! This is one of our favourite cities and we've spent 2 months eating our way around Istanbul to create this series. This 4 part series is about showing you more of the unusual Turkish foods and hunting down where the locals eat. Watch our previous Istanbul series here: https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLg-t2nQXCum5H6OdIDcl7QRM48xidTQPS\n\nThis is our first Istanbul food video. We start with the best pide in the city at a simple pide salonu in Fatih. We love the pide here for its crispy, crunchy dough and fresh ingredients. Next up is a traditional Turkish drink called boza. Boza is a fermented drink made of bulgur, water and sugar. It's commonly drunk in the winter as it's very filling and warming. We sample it at a heritage shop that's been around since 1876- it's said Ataturk drunk boza here once! \n\nOnwards for ca\u011f kebab where lamb is roasted on a horizontal spit, sliced onto a skewer and then crisped up over charcoal. Eaten with lavash (flatbread) and ezme a Turkish salad of tomatoes, parsley, onion and pomegranate molasses, the lamb is absolutely mouthwatering. Our final stop is for a pickle juice at a tursu (pickle) shop in Kadikoy which has been around since 1935. Pickles are a big part of Turkish food culture and almost every meal will include some form of pickled vegetable. We down a pickle juice and some pickles to help us digest all the mouthwatering food we've eaten. \n\nWe hope you enjoyed this Istanbul food tour! Thanks for watching and if you want to see more content like this don't forget to subscribe. #turkishfood #istanbulstreetfood #istanbulfood\n\nWhat we ate and where we ate it:\n\nPide at Pak Pide Pizza Salonu, Mercan, Nasuhiye Sk. Next up is a traditional Turkish drink called boza. Boza is a fermented drink made of bulgur, water and sugar. It's commonly drunk in the winter as it's very filling and warming. Watch the best rally drivers battle on gravel and asphalt roads with mud, rain, dust, ice and heat! Watch high speed action as the rally drivers power slide and drift round narrow corners, go flat out over a big jump or through a watersplash, handbrake turn round a hairpin, survive a big moment, or have a massive crash! Rally requires maximum attack and careful tactics to become world rally champion.  \n\nEach rally has timed sections called special stages, on closed roads.  Drivers complete these stages as quickly as possible. A co-driver reads pace notes that explain the hazards ahead. Rally drivers use the same rally car to travel to each stage on public roads, following normal traffic regulations. The crew which completes all the stages in the shortest time is the rally winner. Championship points are won using the same scoring system as Formula 1. The championship is administered by F\u00e9d\u00e9ration Internationale de l'Automobile (FIA), motorsport's world governing body.\n\nOver 30 countries have hosted WRC rallies. Rally Monte Carlo, Rally Argentina, Rally Finland, Rally Portugal, Tour de Corse on Corsica, France, Rally Sardegna on Sardinia, Italy, Safari Rally in Kenya, Acropolis Rally in Greece, Rally New Zealand, Rally Australia, Rally Japan, Rally GB, Rally Catalunya, Rallye Deutschland, Rally Mexico and many more.  \n\nSome of the world's greatest drivers have won the FIA World Rally Championship for Drivers, like Colin McRae, Carlos Sainz, Walter R\u00f6hrl, Stig Blomqvist, Petter Solberg, Ott T\u00e4nak. The list of world rally champions includes many Finnish rally drivers like Juha Kankkunen, Tommi M\u00e4kinen,  Ari Vatanen, Marcus Gr\u00f6nholm, Hannu Mikkola. French drivers have had success with S\u00e9bastien Ogier, and 9 times world champion S\u00e9bastien Loeb. Famous drivers from other motorsports have come to try rally driving like Ken Block from Rallycross, and Robert Kubica and Kimi R\u00e4ikk\u00f6nen from F1.\n\nCar companies compete for the prestigious FIA World Rally Championship for Manufacturers awarded to the most successful WRC constructor. Winners include Citroen, Hyundai, Volkswagen and Peugeot. Ford have had success with the Ford Escort, Ford Focus and Ford Fiesta when the M-Sport team won in 2017.\nThe 1980's featured the iconic Group B rally cars like the Lancia 037 and Delta S4, Peugeot 205 T16, MG Metro 6R4, Ford RS200 and Audi Quattro.\nJapan dominated the 1990s with the Mitsubishi Lancer, Subaru Impreza, and Toyota Celica and Toyota Corolla. Toyota returned to the WRC in 2017 with the Toyota Yaris WRC, winning in 2018. The 2019 championship was won by Hyundai with the Hyundai i20 Coupe WRC. of Hasroun: Old Town, Touristic and Welcoming in North Lebanon Mountains\n\nHasroun (also Hasrun or Hasroon, Arabic: \u062d\u0635\u0631\u0648\u0646 ) is a village located in the Bsharri District in the North Governorate of Lebanon. It is situated in the Valley of Qadisha, overlooking the southern branch of this valley, the Qannoubine Valley. It owes its nickname of the Rose of Mount Lebanon to its predominantly red-tiled roof houses. The population is Maronite Catholic. Hasroun gave the Maronite Church two Patriarchs, Patriarch Jacob Aouad (1705-1733) and Patriarch Simon Aouad (1743-1756). From Hasroun came also the noted family of orientalists, the Assemani, among them the famous Giuseppe Simone Assemani, author of Bibliotheca Orientalis and Ephraemi Syri opera omnia quae There are eight historical churches, including: Saint Joseph Church, which was completed on September 15, 1914; Our Lady of the Tower Church, which was built on the ruins of the temple of Jupiter; Saint Georges; Saint Nohra; Saint Michel, old and new; Saint Elie; Our Lady of Cultivation. The town serves as the center of the archbishopric of Baalbek\u2013Deir El-Ahmar.\n\nDeir el Ahmar's climate is mild during spring and autumn, dry and warm in summer, and cold during winter. For this reason, some roads leading to the town may be temporarily closed during this period. Ashura is a healthy dessert filled with beans, dried fruits, whole grain wheat sweetened with sugar and spices and cooked in one pot. It is customary to share it with others.\nLet me give you a little bit about history and the importance of Ashura. Muslims around the world are celebrating Ashura, the tenth day of Muharram, which is the first month of the Islamic calendar.\n\nThe word Ashura literally translates to \"10\", indicating the date of the holiday. Some Shia Muslims observe the day to mourn the death of Hussein, the Prophet Muhammad's grandson, at the Battle of Karbala on Muharram 10, about 1,400 years ago. Sunni Muslims observe Ashura commemorate three events: The day Noah was said to have left the Ark, the day Moses and his people were saved from the Pharaoh and the arrival of the Prophet Muhammad's migration from Mecca to Medina in AD 622.\nMuslims voluntarily fast from sunrise to sunset on the day of Ashura, following the example of the Prophet Muhammad. It has said that the first version of 'a\u015fure' was made by Noah himself. It is a special customary dessert that you cook in a big pot and shares with others.\nIngredients For Ashura:\n1+1/2 cups whole grain wheat (A\u015furelik Bu\u011fday)\n3 tbsp rice\n1/2 cup each uncooked white beans and chickpeas (If you use canned use more than 1 cup and add it in the last 10 minutes of cooking)\n1 cup each dried apricots, figs (cut in cubes) and raisins\nAbout 2-3 cups sugar (as much as you desire)\nAbout 6 liters hot water (Will be used as much as needed for the consistency)\nFlavoring options:\n3-4 cloves boiled in half cup water \n1 cinnamon stick\norange rinds\nrose water\nYou can also add: apples, quince (peeled and cut in cubes), cooked Chesnut pieces, whole peeled almonds, and hazelnuts\nTo decorate:  \nHazelnuts, walnuts, pinenuts, unsweetened coconut flakes, ground cinnamon, sliced dried figs and apricots, pomegranates, pistachio nuts..\n\nFor more Turkish Cuisine recipes don't forget to subscribe and press the notification button: "Ashura \"A\u015fure\" is an authentic Turkish dessert that is believed that it is first made by Prophet Noah to gather all of the remaining foodstuffs to make this sweet pudding when he and his family left the ark. Ashura is a healthy dessert filled with beans, dried fruits, whole grain wheat sweetened with sugar and spices and cooked in one pot. It is customary to share it with others.\nLet me give you a little bit about history and the importance of Ashura. Muslims around the world are celebrating Ashura, the tenth day of Muharram, which is the first month of the Islamic calendar.\n\nThe word Ashura literally translates to \"10\", indicating the date of the holiday. Some Shia Muslims observe the day to mourn the death of Hussein, the Prophet Muhammad's grandson, at the Battle of Karbala on Muharram 10, about 1,400 years ago. Sunni Muslims observe Ashura commemorate three events: The day Noah was said to have left the Ark, the day Moses and his people were saved from the Pharaoh and the arrival of the Prophet Muhammad's migration from Mecca to Medina in AD 622.\nMuslims voluntarily fast from sunrise to sunset on the day of Ashura, following the example of the Prophet Muhammad. It has said that the first version of 'a\u015fure' was made by Noah himself. It is a special customary dessert that you cook in a big pot and shares with others.\nIngredients For Ashura:\n1+1/2 cups whole grain wheat (A\u015furelik Bu\u011fday)\n3 tbsp rice\n1/2 cup each uncooked white beans and chickpeas (If you use canned use more than 1 cup and add it in the last 10 minutes of cooking)\n1 cup each dried apricots, figs (cut in cubes) and raisins\nAbout 2-3 cups sugar (as much as you desire)\nAbout 6 liters hot water (Will be used as much as needed for the consistency)\nFlavoring options:\n3-4 cloves boiled in half cup water \n1 cinnamon stick\norange rinds\nrose water\nYou can also add: apples, quince (peeled and cut in cubes), cooked Chesnut pieces, whole peeled almonds, and hazelnuts\nTo decorate:  \nHazelnuts, walnuts, pinenuts, unsweetened coconut flakes, ground cinnamon, sliced dried figs and apricots, pomegranates, pistachio nuts..\n\nFor more Turkish Cuisine recipes don't forget to subscribe and press the notification button: https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCwVIj-OqEjXNqKpItChRrMQ?sub_confirmation=1\n\nFollow me from on social media and website\nINSTAGRAM: www.instagram.com/turkishfoodrecipes_\nFacebook:  https://www.facebook.com/Turkish-Food-Recipes-By-Aysenur-Altan-2260285014289866/"}, "defaultAudioLanguage": "en"}, "contentDetails": {"duration": "PT10M16S", "dimension": "2d", "definition": "hd", "caption": "false", "licensedContent": true, "contentRating": {}, "projection": "rectangular"}, "statistics": {"viewCount": "119461", "likeCount": "3314", "dislikeCount": "58", "favoriteCount": "0", "commentCount": "472"}, "recordingDetails": {"locationDescription": "\u0130stanbul", "location": {"latitude": 41.0082376, "longitude": 28.9783589, "altitude": 0}}}, {"kind": "youtube#video", "etag": "0dOBPhYe1XBYMNXWaFP__vdMT8E", "id": "SDc6VqBz2kk", "snippet": {"publishedAt": "2019-10-02T19:11:18Z", "channelId": "UC67Mr2Bn7TYyDFLhPRY2URw", "title": "Fon Perde Montaj\u0131 Nas\u0131l Yap\u0131l\u0131r ? https://facebook.com/ortobiyoloji\n\u27a4\u0130nstagram : https://instagram.com/ortobiyoloji\n\nMenisk\u00fcs y\u0131rt\u0131klar\u0131 nas\u0131l te\u015fhis edilir?\nani geli\u015fen travmatik menisk\u00fcs y\u0131rt\u0131klar\u0131nda hasta baca\u011f\u0131ndaki \u015fi\u015flik toparlama ve a\u011fr\u0131yla acil poliklini\u011fe ba\u015fvurur.  S\u0131kl\u0131kla ya\u015fl\u0131larda kar\u015f\u0131m\u0131za \u00e7\u0131kan dejeneratif y\u0131rt\u0131klarda hasta mikro y\u0131rt\u0131klar\u0131n zamanla b\u00fcy\u00fcyerek \u015fikayet edecek boyuta geldi\u011finde hekime ba\u015fvurur.\nyap\u0131lan fizik muayenede eklem b\u00f6lgesinde a\u011fr\u0131 \u015fi\u015flik hassasiyet diz eklem hareketlerinde s\u0131k\u0131\u015ft\u0131rma tesislerinde menisk\u00fcs y\u0131rt\u0131\u011f\u0131 \u015f\u00fcphesi olu\u015fturur.\nklinik tan\u0131 koymada alt\u0131n standart manyetik rezonans g\u00f6r\u00fcnt\u00fcleme tekni\u011fidir.\nmanyetik rezonans inceleme ile elde edilen g\u00f6r\u00fcnt\u00fcler klinik muayene ile birlikte de\u011ferlendirmeli y\u0131rt\u0131\u011f\u0131n hastan\u0131n ya\u015f\u0131 tarif edilen travma ile olan ili\u015fkisi yeni ya da eski olup olmad\u0131\u011f\u0131 birlikte ba\u011f hasar\u0131 ya da kemik ve k\u0131k\u0131rdak dokuda ek yaralanma olup olmad\u0131\u011f\u0131 de\u011ferlendirmelidir.\nManyetik rezonans incelemesinin raporlanmas\u0131\ng\u00fcn\u00fcm\u00fczde \u00e7ok s\u0131k kullan\u0131lan bir radyolojik de\u011ferlendirme y\u00f6ntemi olan manyetik rezonans sonras\u0131 hastalar\u0131n raporlar\u0131nda kendi sa\u011fl\u0131k durumlar\u0131n\u0131 ait bilgileri okuyarak fikir sahibi olmaya \u00e7al\u0131\u015ft\u0131klar\u0131 g\u00f6zlenmektedir.\nradyoloji uzmanlar\u0131n\u0131n yazd\u0131\u011f\u0131 bu raporlarda kayda ge\u00e7irilen bilgilerin hepsi her zaman klinik ve uyumlu olmayabilir ya da hepsi tedavi de\u011feri ta\u015f\u0131mayabilir. \u00f6rne\u011fin evre 1 evre 2 menisk\u00fcs yaralanmalar\u0131 menisk\u00fcs dokusunun i\u00e7erisindeki manyetik rezonans sinirlenmedeki farkl\u0131l\u0131klar\u0131 g\u00f6sterirken evre 3 ve 4 hasarlar mekanik sorun yapabilecek bir menisk\u00fcs y\u0131rt\u0131\u011f\u0131n\u0131n i\u015faret\u00e7isidir.\nhastalar\u0131n raporlu g\u00f6rd\u00fckleri \u00f6zellikle d\u00fc\u015f\u00fck evre menisk\u00fcs hasarlar\u0131nda endi\u015fe etmemeleri hekimlerine dan\u0131\u015farak ameliyat d\u0131\u015f\u0131 y\u00f6ntemleri daha \u00f6n planda d\u00fc\u015f\u00fcnmeleri \u00f6nerilmektedir. ileri evre y\u0131rt\u0131klarda ya da y\u0131rt\u0131\u011f\u0131n ba\u015fka yaralanma tipleri ile karma\u015f\u0131k hale geldi\u011fi durumlarda artroskopik halk tabiriyle kapal\u0131 ameliyat teknikleri kullan\u0131lmaktad\u0131r.\nArtroskopi nedir?\nArtroskopi k\u00f6ken olarak yabanc\u0131 bir kelime olup artro eklem skopi g\u00f6zlemlemek olarak iki farkl\u0131 kelimenin birle\u015fmesiyle olu\u015fmu\u015f yabanc\u0131 bir isim tamlamas\u0131d\u0131r.\nsadece eklem i\u00e7erisinin g\u00f6zlenmesi anlam\u0131na gelmiyor bu s\u0131rada da yap\u0131lacak muayene ile eklem i\u00e7erisindeki dokular\u0131n kalitesi dayan\u0131kl\u0131 hasara kar\u015f\u0131 geli\u015fmi\u015f oldu\u011fu direnci de\u011ferlendirilir. yap\u0131lan ameliyat i\u00e7i de\u011ferlendirme neticesinde ayn\u0131 seansta tedavi edici giri\u015fimlerde yap\u0131labilmektedir. Eklem i\u00e7inin y\u0131kanmas\u0131 eklem i\u00e7erisinde varsa serbest cisimlerin \u00e7\u0131kar\u0131lmas\u0131 s\u0131kl\u0131kla ba\u015far\u0131 ile uygulan\u0131r. menisk\u00fcs dokusunda y\u0131rt\u0131klar varsa dikilmeyecek kadar par\u00e7al\u0131 y\u0131rt\u0131klarsa \u00e7\u0131kar\u0131lmas\u0131 \u00f6nerilir.\nNe yaz\u0131k ki bu durumda menisk\u00fcs dokusunda geri d\u00f6n\u00fc\u015f\u00fcms\u00fcz bir kay\u0131p s\u00f6z konusudur.\ng\u00fcn\u00fcm\u00fczde Se\u00e7kin tedavi \u015fekli menisk\u00fcs y\u0131rt\u0131klar\u0131n\u0131n dikilmesi dir menisk\u00fcs v\u00fccuttan at\u0131lacak gereksiz bir organ par\u00e7as\u0131 de\u011fildir.aksi takdirde eklemi koruyucu yap\u0131s\u0131 ortadan kalkarak eklemde erken d\u00f6nemde harabiyet halk tabiriyle kire\u00e7lenmeden en ileri d\u00f6nen eklem hasar\u0131 ortaya \u00e7\u0131kar.\nMenisk\u00fcs y\u0131rt\u0131klar\u0131n\u0131n tedavisi\nt\u00fcm menisk\u00fcs y\u0131rt\u0131klar\u0131n\u0131n bir kelimesi gerekmektedir erken evre hasarlarda eklem i\u00e7ine yap\u0131lacak mezenkimal k\u00f6k h\u00fccre uygulamalar\u0131 ya da trombositten zenginle\u015ftirilmi\u015f plazma yayg\u0131n ad\u0131 ile PRP menisk\u00fcs dokusunda olu\u015fturdu\u011fu rejeneratif de\u011fi\u015fiklikler de hasarl\u0131 geri d\u00f6nd\u00fcrebilmek d\u0131\u015far\u0131 ka\u00e7arak menisk\u00fcs kisti ne neden oldu\u011fu g\u00f6zlenmektedir bu gibi durumlarda kist i\u00e7eri\u011finin enjekt\u00f6rle aspir edilmesi ve bu b\u00f6lgeden The city is situated on the Seyhan river, 35 km inland from the Mediterranean, in south-central Anatolia. "2019-07-19T17:45:19Z", "channelId": "UCwVIj-OqEjXNqKpItChRrMQ", "title": "Istanbul Spice Bazaar, Coppersmith | Turkish Kofta | Candy Baklava Shops", "description": "In this Istanbul Trip i am searching for best places to shop copper pans, looking for coppersmith bazaar. I begin my trip from Sirkeci Train Station passing through some old and famous baklava and candy shops and Spice Bazaar in Eminonu. I go to Sultanhamam and Beyazit to find the copper shops and return to Sultanahmet to eat at a local Turkish restaurant Sultanahmet Koftecisi.\n\nHere are the location links in from the video:\nSirkeci Train Station: https://goo.gl/maps/wnYwXUCY7BjpTR1a7\nKara Mustafa Pasha Mosque: https://goo.gl/maps/x55gjPCmchULkqwW8\nTrabzon Copper Bazaar: https://goo.gl/maps/1CZbhdJ3Zjzw8n9d6\nKastamonu Copper Bazaar: https://goo.gl/maps/mi5DEt13kkeLqcfa8\nSpice Bazaar: https://goo.gl/maps/8zBMnhSt1cqzvQJC7\n\u00c7emberlitas: https://goo.gl/maps/UXL6h18MyptW6kau9\nSultanahmet Koftecisi: https://goo.gl/maps/GV4xzS3dZCQswKG38\n\nAbout Akide Candy (Traditional Hard Candy)\nAkide candy and Turkish delight are two of the most important culinary heritages of Turkey.  Akide candy was invented in 16th century at a time when sugar was very expensive and more valuable than honey. The word \u201cakide\u201d comes from Arabic and means \u201cfaith and loyalty.\u201d In Syrian Arabic dialect, it means \u201cthickening, making a knot.\u201d Therefore the candy that is made by boiling honey or sugar took on the name \u201cakide.\u201d  \n\nLater on, akide\u2019s alternative meanings; faith and loyalty were picked up and akide candy took on a symbolic meaning. The janissary army would go to the place every 3 months to receive their salary, which was held in a ceremonial manner. The highest ranking janissary officers would offer this candy to the Grand Vizier and other dignitaries to symbolize their loyalty to the state and the sultan. It also became a tradition to offer akide candy to the members of the Imperial Council after the morning prayers every Tuesday, and akide candy became an important part of every type of social and religious celebrations as well as weddings and circumcision ceremonies. \n\nThe ingredients of akide candy are quite simple, yet making it requires a certain amount of expertise. Sugar with some water is heated up to about 175-180C (350F). Sugar has to be melted completely and come to an almost caramel consistency and poured on a marble counter. Marble is crucial in this process as the natural cooling effects will help with the cooling of the melted sugar and bring it to the right consistency to make the candy.   At this stage the aromatics (e.g. mastic, mint, lemon, rose petals, pistachio, cinnamon, clove etc.) are added to the sugar and the kneading process starts that helps to bring down the temperature of the sugar, makes it pliable and incorporates the aromatics. When the cooling sugar comes to about 70C (160F) the shaping of the candy starts. Timing is very crucial in this process as the sugar hardens as it cools, so help from a heat lamp or a table with bottom heat is needed. The end product is the colorful little hard candies that are like little gems.\n\nOne of the most important discoveries of Turkish confectionery, akide candy is a cultural symbol of \u201ceating sweet and talking sweet\u201d (a famous Turkish saying).\n\nSource:\n\nMary I\u015f\u0131n, Sherbet and Spice, The Complete Story of Turkish Sweets and Desserts, Mary I\u015f\u0131n, I.B.Tauris, London "description": "ISTANBUL STREET FOOD | Massive MEZZE feast, ROASTED SHEEP'S HEAD | Delicious TURKISH FOOD \nWe're in Istanbul, Turkey! This is one of our favourite cities and we've spent 2 months eating our way around Istanbul to create this series. This 4 part series is about showing you the best Istanbul street food and hunting down local food and heritage Turkish shops and restaurants which are Istanbul icons. Watch our previous Istanbul series here: https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLg-t2nQXCum5H6OdIDcl7QRM48xidTQPS\n\nThis is our third Istanbul food video. We start with tantuni, a popular Istanbul street food which comes from the southern town of Mersin. Made up of fried diced beef, parsley, onions and spice all wrapped up in a soft lavas- this is a tasty snack, simple but full of flavour. Next up we head into the laneways of Beyoglu to find a small stall outside a butcher shop where you can eat kelle tandir or roasted sheep's head. Onwards for pudding! Milk puddings play a rich part in Turkey's food culture and date back to the Ottoman empire where puddings were often made with shredded chicken and cornflour. This tradition has continued and we eat a chicken and milk pudding called kazandibi and s\u00fctla\u00e7, a milky rice pudding from a restaurant that's famous for their puddings. Finally we head for one of our favourite Turkish meals- meze! Mezze is made up of a number of small savoury plates- both hot and cold which you graze on as you drink. We order raki- Turkey's national spirit and share a number of small plates from hamsi (anchovies) to dips. \n\nWe hope you enjoyed this Istanbul street food tour! Thanks for watching and if you want to see more content like this don't forget to subscribe.#turkishfood #istanbulstreetfood #istanbulfood\n\nWhat we ate and where we ate it:\n\nTantuni at  Suat Usta Mersin Tantuni, Katip Mustafa \u00c7elebi, Tel Sk. No:1, 34433 Beyo\u011flu/\u0130stanbul. No:18, 34435 Beyo\u011flu/\u0130stanbul. Temel g\u00f6revi diz ekleminin i\u00e7 ve d\u0131\u015f\u0131na gelen y\u00fckleri ta\u015f\u0131makt\u0131r.\n\n\u00d6n \u00c7apraz Ba\u011flar\n\u00d6n ve arka \u00e7apraz ba\u011f olmak \u00fczere her dizde 2 adet bulunur. Konum olarak birbirlerine \u00e7apraz olacak \u015fekilde diz ekleminin i\u00e7inde yer al\u0131rlar. Dizin \u00f6n ve arka k\u0131sm\u0131na gelen y\u00fckleri ta\u015f\u0131y\u0131p d\u00f6nme hareketleri i\u00e7inde diz eklemini koruma g\u00f6revini \u00fcstlenirler.\n\n\u00d6n \u00e7apraz ba\u011f\u0131m\u0131z, kaval kemi\u011finin \u00fcst k\u0131sm\u0131ndan ba\u015flay\u0131p diz bo\u015flu\u011fundan ge\u00e7erek uyluk kemi\u011finin alt k\u0131sm\u0131na dizimizin tam ortas\u0131ndan ge\u00e7ecek \u015fekilde konumlanm\u0131\u015ft\u0131r. Ba\u015fl\u0131ca g\u00f6revi kaval kemi\u011finin, uyluk kemi\u011finin alt\u0131ndan \u00f6ne do\u011fru hareket etmesinin engellemek ve diz eklemini korumakt\u0131r.\n\n\u00d6n \u00c7apraz Ba\u011f Yaralanmalar\u0131\n\u00c7apraz ba\u011f yaralanmalar\u0131 genellikle \u00f6n \u00e7apraz ba\u011flarda olu\u015fur. sportif etkinliklerde olu\u015fmakla birlikte kaval kemi\u011finin uyluk kemi\u011fi alt\u0131ndan \u00f6ne do\u011fru zorlanmas\u0131yla olur. Bu tip zorlu hareketler ba\u011f\u0131n fazla gerilmesine ve yaralanmas\u0131na sebep olur.\n\nFutbol ve kayak sporuyla ilgilenenler diz eklemlerini ani d\u00f6n\u00fc\u015fler, dizi zorlay\u0131c\u0131 y\u00fck ve darbelere maruz b\u0131rakt\u0131\u011f\u0131 i\u00e7in \u00f6n \u00e7apraz ba\u011f yaralanmalar\u0131n\u0131 ya\u015farlar.\n\n\u00d6n \u00e7apraz ba\u011f yaralanmalar\u0131 kad\u0131n sporcularda erkek sporculara oranla daha s\u0131k olu\u015fur ve nedeni erkek bacak kaslar\u0131n\u0131n kad\u0131nlara oranla daha g\u00fc\u00e7l\u00fc olmas\u0131d\u0131r. Unutmayal\u0131m ki bacak kaslar\u0131m\u0131z dizlerimize binen y\u00fck\u00fcn azalmas\u0131n\u0131 sa\u011flar.\n\n\u00d6n \u00c7apraz Ba\u011f Yaralanmas\u0131 Belirtileri\n\u00c7apraz ba\u011f yaralanmas\u0131 esnas\u0131nda dizden bir kopma oldu\u011funu d\u00fc\u015f\u00fcnmemize sebep olacak kadar belirgin ses duyulabilir. Sonras\u0131ndaki ilk belirtiler diz a\u011fr\u0131s\u0131 ve dizde \u015fi\u015fme \u015feklinde olur. \u015ei\u015fli\u011fin sebebi yaralanma sonras\u0131nda olu\u015fan eklem i\u00e7i kanamadan dolay\u0131 olur. Yaralanma s\u0131ras\u0131nda ve sonras\u0131nda k\u0131k\u0131rdak ve menisk\u00fcs dokular\u0131 zarar g\u00f6rmediyse \u015fi\u015flik ve a\u011fr\u0131lar zamanla azal\u0131r. \u00c7apraz ba\u011f yaralanmas\u0131ndan sonra hasta dizinde bo\u015fluk hisseder ve diz eklemi g\u00fc\u00e7s\u00fczle\u015fir.\n\n\u00d6n \u00c7apraz Ba\u011f Yaralanmas\u0131 Te\u015fhisi\n\u00d6n \u00e7apraz ba\u011f yaralanmas\u0131 te\u015fhisi hastan\u0131n travma \u00f6yk\u00fcs\u00fc dinlenir, fiziki ortopedi muayenesi yap\u0131l\u0131r ve  diz MR\u2019\u0131 de\u011ferlendirilerek konulur. Mr e\u015fli\u011finde muayenede \u00e7apraz ba\u011f yaralanmas\u0131n\u0131n yan\u0131nda menisk\u00fcs ve k\u0131k\u0131rdak dokular\u0131ndaki hasarlarda belirlenir.\n\n\u00d6n \u00c7apraz Ba\u011f Tedavisi\n\u00d6n \u00e7apraz ba\u011f yaralanmalar\u0131ndan sonra uygulanacak tedavinin belirlenmesinde hastan\u0131n ya\u015fant\u0131s\u0131 \u00f6nemlidir. Hasta sporcuysa ve spora devam etmesi gerekiyorsa hedef sportif etkinliklerini yapabilmesini sa\u011flamak olurken, spor yapmayan bir hasta i\u00e7in g\u00fcnl\u00fck ya\u015fant\u0131s\u0131na d\u00f6nmesini sa\u011flayacak en uygun tedavi se\u00e7ilmelidir. Sporcularda genellikle cerrahi tedavilere ba\u015fvurulur bunun sebebi ise cerrahi tedaviler biyolojik tedavilere oranla daha h\u0131zl\u0131 sonu\u00e7 verir.\n\n\u00d6n \u00c7apraz Ba\u011f Cerrahi D\u0131\u015f\u0131 Tedavi\n\u00d6n \u00e7apraz ba\u011f yaralanmalar\u0131nda cerrahi d\u0131\u015f\u0131 tedaviler k\u0131smi yaralanmas\u0131 olan, sportif faaliyetleri olmayan ve iyile\u015fmek i\u00e7in zaman\u0131 olan ki\u015filer i\u00e7in uygundur. Prp ve k\u00f6k h\u00fccre tedavileri cerrahi d\u0131\u015f\u0131 tedavilerin ba\u015f\u0131nda gelir. Bu tedaviler hasarl\u0131 ba\u011flarda doku iyile\u015fmesi ba\u015flat\u0131r. Uygun hasta grubunda olduk\u00e7a etkili tedavilerdir.\n\nFizik tedavi ve istirahat ile de diz eklemine binen y\u00fck azalt\u0131l\u0131p, kaslar kuvvetlendirilerek hastalar\u0131n \u015fikayetleri azalt\u0131labilir.\n\n\u00d6n \u00c7apraz Ba\u011f Cerrahi Tedavi\nCerrahi tedaviler zorunlu hallerde yap\u0131l\u0131r ve en son ba\u015fvurulan tedavilerdir. Gereklilik \u015fartlar\u0131 olu\u015fmadan cerrahi tedavilere ba\u015fvurmamak gerekir. V\u00fccudun do\u011fall\u0131\u011f\u0131n\u0131 korumak tedavilerde birinci \u00f6ncelik olmal\u0131d\u0131r. Very popular among ladies in tea parties here in Turkey :) \nThe main ingredient is thin bulgur. It also has onion, tomato paste, olive oil and spices along with red lentils of course. For fresh ingredients, I used just chopped parsley as a fresh green but in original we also use finely sliced scallions too.\n\nIngredients for Lentil Kofta Balls\n1 cup red lentils (wash and drained)\n2+1/2 cups water\na good pinch of salt\n1 cup thin bulgur wheat\n1 big onion\n5-6 tbsp olive oil\nlittle less than 1 tbsp tomato paste\nlittle less than red pepper paste (If you can't find use tomato paste instead)\n1 tsp paprika\n1 tsp or more salt\n2 tsp ground cumin\n1/3 bunch of parsley\n5-6 thin scallions\nTo serve: fresh lettuce leaves, lemon wedges\n\nMethod:\nWash and drain the lentils and cook in 2+1/2 cups water with a pinch of salt in a pot or pressure cooker to make it quicker with the lid on until lentils are very soft like a mashy puree.\nTurn off the heat and while it is still hot, add the bulgur wheat, stir well and close to lid. Wait until the bulgur soaks all the juices.\n Meanwhile, prepare the sauce. Chop the onion finely and saute in 5-6 tbsp olive oil until it gets a bit color.\nAdd tomato and if you have pepper paste. Continue to saute until the raw smell of the tomato and pepper paste is gone about 3-4 minutes on medium-low heat.\nAdd salt, paprika and cumin, and then 1/4 cup of water. Simmer for about 1 minute and add the sauce to the lentil and bulgur mixture.\nMix everything well, you can also mash it with your hand. Give it a taste if it needs more seasonings and salt. Drizzle 3-4 tbsp more olive oil and mix well. The consistency we are looking for is like thick wet sand that you can shape it. If it seems too dry you can add little more water or olive oil for extra taste and adjust it. You can also check it by shaping a piece.\nFinally, add finely chopped parsley and scallions if using and mix again without mashing the greens too much.\nShape the lentil kofta balls as you wish and serve with lots of lettuce leaves and lemon wedges and enjoy! Afiyet Olsun!\n\nWhat Is Bulgur Wheat?\nBulgur is a cereal grain made from dried, cracked wheat \u2014 most commonly durum wheat. It is partially cooked so that it can be prepared relatively quickly. When cooked, it has a similar consistency to couscous or quinoa.\n\nBulgur is considered a whole grain, meaning that the entire wheat kernel \u2014 including the germ, endosperm and bran \u2014 is eaten.\n\nIt is originated in the Mediterranean and can be traced back thousands of years. To this day, it\u2019s a staple ingredient in many Turkish, Middle Eastern and Mediterranean dishes.\n\nYou might be interested in this similar recipe Cigkofte (Turkish raw meatless bulgur balls): https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=isohRsOHfJg\n\nFor more Turkish Cuisine recipes don't forget to subscribe and press the notification button: https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCwVIj-OqEjXNqKpItChRrMQ?sub_confirmation=1\n\nFollow me from on social media and website\nINSTAGRAM: www.instagram.com/turkishfoodrecipes_\nFacebook:  https://www.facebook.com/Turkish-Food-Recipes-By-Aysenur-Altan-2260285014289866/", "thumbnails": {"default": {"url": "https://i.ytimg.com/vi/vqyOR4-MVH8/default.jpg", "width": 120, "height": 90}, "medium": {"url": "https://i.ytimg.com/vi/vqyOR4-MVH8/mqdefault.jpg", "width": 320, "height": 180}, "high": {"url": "https://i.ytimg.com/vi/vqyOR4-MVH8/hqdefault.jpg", "width": 480, "height": 360}, "standard": {"url": "https://i.ytimg.com/vi/vqyOR4-MVH8/sddefault.jpg", "width": 640, "height": 480}, "maxres": {"url": "https://i.ytimg.com/vi/vqyOR4-MVH8/maxresdefault.jpg", "width": 1280, "height": 720}}, "channelTitle": "Turkish Food Travel", "tags": ["turkish food", "turkish recipes", "turkish cuisine", "turkish recipes in english", "lentil recipe", "lentil kofte turkish", "lentil kofta recipe", "lentil kofta balls", "lentil kofte", "vegan balls recipe", "vegan kofta", "mercimek k\u00f6ftesi", "vegan turkish recipes", "vegan turkish food", "bulgur wheat recipe"], "categoryId": "26", "liveBroadcastContent": "none", "localized": {"title": "Turkish Lentil Kofta Balls | Mercimek K\u00f6ftesi (Vegan) By Aysenur Altan", "description": "Turkish Lentil Kofta \"Mercimek K\u00f6ftesi\" is easy to make and delicious vegan dishes with simple ingredients. Karaci\u011fer ya\u011flanmas\u0131na ne iyi gelir, neler yapmal\u0131y\u0131z gibi sorular\u0131n\u0131za madde madde uygulayabilece\u011finiz \u015fekilde anlatt\u0131m.\n\nSizde, kilo vermekte merak etti\u011finiz konular\u0131 veya sorular\u0131n\u0131z\u0131 l\u00fctfen videonun alt\u0131na yorum olarak yaz\u0131n.\n\nKaraci\u011fer Ya\u011flanmas\u0131 Varsa, Ne Yap\u0131l\u0131r? \n1. It is not a wedding if we don't have keshkek at our wedding as Birgul coats.\nIngredients to make Keshkek\n3 cups cracked wheat (yarma bu\u011fday)\n500 gr. beef (breferable from the thigh or soft meat without fat) You can also use meat with bone \nabout 2+1/2 liter hot water\nTo fry the meat 2 tbsp butter\nFor the sauce:\n4 tbsp butter\nhot or sweet red pepper flakes if you prefer\nHere is Gozleme recipe video, with the local lady Youtuber Aunt Sadiye in Kastamonu\u00c7 https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=iuvg87N0ias \nFor more Turkish Cuisine recipes don't forget to subscribe and press the notification button: https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCwVIj-OqEjXNqKpItChRrMQ?sub_confirmation=1\n\nFollow me from on social media and website\nINSTAGRAM: www.instagram.com/turkishfoodrecipes_\nFacebook:  https://www.facebook.com/Turkish-Food-Recipes-By-Aysenur-Altan-2260285014289866/"}, "defaultAudioLanguage": "en"}, "contentDetails": {"duration": "PT12M4S", "dimension": "2d", "definition": "hd", "caption": "false", "licensedContent": true, "contentRating": {}, "projection": "rectangular"}, "statistics": {"viewCount": "53877", "likeCount": "1719", "dislikeCount": "34", "favoriteCount": "0", "commentCount": "366"}, "recordingDetails": {"locationDescription": "Didim", "location": {"latitude": 37.376094, "longitude": 27.264729, "altitude": 0}}}, {"kind": "youtube#video", "etag": "I1miYPPIKT4okuJbMn-3j0GfZno", "id": "iAwr2Ncm5zE", "snippet": {"publishedAt": "2019-09-23T18:31:11Z", "channelId": "UCmP__pZ-wiLSMm-4t1Z8mMg", "title": "THINGS TO KNOW BEFORE VISITING ISTANBUL, TURKEY", "description": "THINGS TO KNOW BEFORE VISITING ISTANBUL, TURKEY. 3 hurma t\u00fcketin.\n2\ufe0f\u20e3Ara \u00f6\u011f\u00fcnde, 1 k\u00fc\u00e7\u00fck dilim tahin helvas\u0131 tercih edin. \n3\ufe0f\u20e3Ana \u00f6\u011f\u00fcnde \u00e7orba t\u00fcketin ve ekmek "UC-a6p2J8e1A_zobKbNKq0vA", "title": "Good Weather Forecast mit Lisa&Lena - Better Days (Official Video)", "description": "\"Better Days\" is the title song of the eponymous charity campaign of the German social media stars \"Lisa & Lena\". The song is not only an encouraging hymn for hope and life - the song is actually changing the world.\nStream or Download the Single: https://t1p.de/betterdays\n\u200b\u200b\n\n\nBetter Days\nMusic and lyrics written by: \nFlorian Stielper, Chris Wahle\nProduction: Chris Wahle \nMix: Kraans de Lutin \nMastering: Kraans de Lutin\n\u00a9 Published by: soundso Musikverlag + Peermusic Sweden\n\u200b\u200bVideo: by Alexander Ronsdorf\n\nStay in touch\nhttps://betterdays.world\nInstagram: https://instagram.com/goodweatherforecast\nFacebook: https://www.facebook.com/goodweatherforecast\nWebsite: http://www.goodweatherforecast.de \nMerchandise: http://www.gwf-shop.de/39202120/startseite\n\nThe song \"Superhumans\" by Good Weather Forecast was an announcement. Now the band lays down. \"Better Days\" - that's the name of the new single. A big, emotional song with a very special story. \"Better Days\" is the title song of the eponymous charity campaign of the German social media stars \"Lisa & Lena\". The song is not only an encouraging hymn for hope and life - the song is actually changing the world. Because the entire profit through streaming and selling goes to a project of the aid organization GAiN, which visited the band together with the twins Lisa & Lena in Armenia in September 2019.\nA rusty tin container juts awkwardly into the cloudless sky . The white sunlight cruelly paves its way through the holey roof and the cracked windows. It is hot. Within the container even hotter. 50 degrees celsius and more. Hard to believe that four kids and their parents live in these  rust-eaten 14 squaremeters...\nCarefully we\u2019re approaching the unreal scenery. We, that\u2019s the twins Lisa and Lena and the five boys from the band Good Weather Forecast. Here we are. Thousands of miles away from our sheltered life in Germany. Here we are in the middle of nowhere between dust and glaring sunlight. Here we are trying to process these rough impressions. But what are we doing here? And how did we end up here in the first place?\nIt all started with a song. One year before. Flo Stielper, singer of the band Good Weather Forecast meets up with his brother John Stielper and the swedish producer and friend \u201eChris Whale\u201c for some songwriting sessions in Hamburg, Nothern Germany. The result is a song - \"Better Days\". \"For me, it was immediately clear that this song is something special,\" says Flo Stielper and continues, \"The song is so vulnerable, so dramatic, and yet this great hopeful anthem rises in the chorus. Like a ray of light in the dark. A melody full of hope and full of life.\u201c\nQuickly the idea of a charity song arises. The band is sure! The song should encourage fans and listeners. And not only that. The song should help children in poverty. Give children hope. The band turns to the humanitarian relief organization GAiN, with which the band has been connected for years.\nAt the same time \u201cLisa and Lena\u201c compete in one Germany\u2019s most succeful tv shows called \u201cKlein gegen Gro\u00df\u201c. The twins win the price money over 30.000 Euros and donate the amount to GAiN. Now it all comes together. Cause Lisa and Lena don\u2019t only want to donate. They want to do more. \u201eWe want to use our influence to do something good\u201c, Lisa tells. And so the idea of a joint campaign is slowly forming - Better Days - giving hope to children.\n\nNow we\u2019re standing here. In Armenia. In front of this rusty container. Now the band lays down. \"Better Days\" - that's the name of the new single. A big, emotional song with a very special story. \"Better Days\" is the title song of the eponymous charity campaign of the German social media stars \"Lisa & Lena\". The song is not only an encouraging hymn for hope and life - the song is actually changing the world. Because the entire profit through streaming and selling goes to a project of the aid organization GAiN, which visited the band together with the twins Lisa & Lena in Armenia in September 2019.\nA rusty tin container juts awkwardly into the cloudless sky . The white sunlight cruelly paves its way through the holey roof and the cracked windows. It is hot. Within the container even hotter. 50 degrees celsius and more. Hard to believe that four kids and their parents live in these  rust-eaten 14 squaremeters...\nCarefully we\u2019re approaching the unreal scenery. We, that\u2019s the twins Lisa and Lena and the five boys from the band Good Weather Forecast. Here we are. Thousands of miles away from our sheltered life in Germany. Here we are in the middle of nowhere between dust and glaring sunlight. Here we are trying to process these rough impressions. But what are we doing here? And how did we end up here in the first place?\nIt all started with a song. One year before. Flo Stielper, singer of the band Good Weather Forecast meets up with his brother John Stielper and the swedish producer and friend \u201eChris Whale\u201c for some songwriting sessions in Hamburg, Nothern Germany. The result is a song - \"Better Days\". \"For me, it was immediately clear that this song is something special,\" says Flo Stielper and continues, \"The song is so vulnerable, so dramatic, and yet this great hopeful anthem rises in the chorus. Like a ray of light in the dark. A melody full of hope and full of life.\u201c\nQuickly the idea of a charity song arises. The band is sure! The song should encourage fans and listeners. And not only that. The song should help children in poverty. Give children hope. The band turns to the humanitarian relief organization GAiN, with which the band has been connected for years.\nAt the same time \u201cLisa and Lena\u201c compete in one Germany\u2019s most succeful tv shows called \u201cKlein gegen Gro\u00df\u201c. The twins win the price money over 30.000 Euros and donate the amount to GAiN. Now it all comes together. Cause Lisa and Lena don\u2019t only want to donate. fakt\u00f6rler, ge\u00e7irilen travmalara ba\u011fl\u0131 olarak kal\u00e7ada olu\u015fan kire\u00e7lenme (osteoartrit), avask\u00fcler nekroz, k\u0131k\u0131rdak azalmas\u0131, k\u0131k\u0131rdak hasar\u0131 gibi rahats\u0131zl\u0131klardan dolay\u0131 kal\u00e7an\u0131n a\u015f\u0131nmas\u0131, eklemin deforme olmas\u0131 temel g\u00f6revlerinden biri olan v\u00fccut y\u00fck\u00fcn\u00fc e\u015fit da\u011f\u0131tma, baca\u011f\u0131n hareketini ba\u015flatma gibi g\u00f6revlerini yapamamas\u0131na sebep olan ve hastan\u0131n ya\u015fam kalitesini bozan kal\u00e7a rahats\u0131zl\u0131klar\u0131nda uygulanan cerrahi tedavidir.\n\nTedavide a\u015f\u0131nm\u0131\u015f le\u011fen kemi\u011finin yuvas\u0131 ile uyluk kemi\u011finin \u00fcst k\u0131sm\u0131 \u00f6zel olarak titanyum, kobalt ve krom gibi \u00e7ok dayan\u0131kl\u0131 metallerden olu\u015fan yapay eklemle de\u011fi\u015ftirilir.\n\nTedavide kal\u00e7an\u0131n hasarl\u0131 k\u0131s\u0131mlar\u0131 tra\u015flanarak protezin yeri haz\u0131rlan\u0131p hastan\u0131n kal\u00e7as\u0131na monte edilerek kal\u00e7a ekleminin yeniden i\u015flevsellik kazanmas\u0131 sa\u011flan\u0131r.\n\nTedavide insan v\u00fccuduyla uyumlu uzun \u00f6m\u00fcrl\u00fc \u00fcr\u00fcnler kullan\u0131l\u0131r. Ameliyat\u0131n amac\u0131 kal\u00e7ay\u0131 eski sa\u011fl\u0131\u011f\u0131na kavu\u015fturmak de\u011fil hastan\u0131n temel hareket fonksiyonlar\u0131n\u0131 yeniden yapabilmesini sa\u011flamakt\u0131r.\n\nKal\u00e7a Protezi Neden Yap\u0131l\u0131r?\nKal\u00e7a protezi ameliyat\u0131 avask\u00fcler nekroz, kire\u00e7lenme ve k\u0131k\u0131rdak kayb\u0131na ba\u011fl\u0131 olarak kal\u00e7a kemikleri aradaki temas\u0131 engelleyen koruyucu k\u0131k\u0131rdak yap\u0131 ortadan kalk\u0131nca birbirlerine s\u00fcrt\u00fcnmeye ba\u011fl\u0131 a\u015f\u0131nmaya ba\u015flar bu a\u015f\u0131nmalar hastan\u0131n ciddi kal\u00e7a a\u011fr\u0131lar\u0131 ya\u015famas\u0131na, rahat hareket edememesine sebep olur. Zamanla kal\u00e7a eklem b\u00fct\u00fcnl\u00fc\u011f\u00fc bozulur. Kal\u00e7a sa\u011fl\u0131\u011f\u0131 bu seviyede bozuldu\u011funda bu durumu cerrahi tedaviler d\u0131\u015f\u0131nda d\u00fczeltmek m\u00fcmk\u00fcn de\u011fildir ve hasta kal\u00e7a protezi ameliyat\u0131 olmak zorunda kal\u0131r.\n\nKal\u00e7a Protezi Kimlere Yap\u0131lmal\u0131d\u0131r?\nkal\u00e7a protezi hastay\u0131 ba\u011flay\u0131c\u0131 bir tedavidir ve bir kez kal\u00e7a protezi tedavisi yap\u0131ld\u0131ktan sonra geri d\u00f6n\u00fc\u015f\u00fc yoktur. Protezden sonra hasta art\u0131k protez ile ya\u015famaya mecbur kal\u0131r. Bu nedenle bu tedavi herhangi bir sebeple kal\u00e7a eklemi i\u015flevini kaybetmi\u015f, anestezi a\u00e7\u0131s\u0131ndan bir risk ta\u015f\u0131mayan her ya\u015ftaki hastaya yap\u0131labilir. kal\u00e7a protezi tedavisi zorunlu olan hasta grubuna uygulanmal\u0131d\u0131r, bu grup genelde 50 \u2013 80 aras\u0131 erkek ve kad\u0131n hastalard\u0131r. Zorunlu olmad\u0131k\u00e7a daha erken ya\u015flarda tercih edilmez.\n\nProtez tedavisi zorunlu hale gelmeden tedavi d\u0131\u015f\u0131 se\u00e7enekler denenmelidir. Bu tedaviler kal\u00e7a protezi ameliyat\u0131na giden s\u00fcreci olduk\u00e7a uzatabilirler fakat ameliyat ihtiyac\u0131n\u0131 tamamen ortadan kald\u0131ramazlar.\n\nKal\u00e7a eklem a\u015f\u0131nmas\u0131n\u0131 engellemek, yava\u015flatmak ve hasta \u015fikayetlerini azaltmak i\u00e7in kal\u00e7aya sinoviyal s\u0131v\u0131 enjeksiyonu, kal\u00e7a eklemine prp tedavisi ve kemik ili\u011fi ya da ya\u011f kaynakl\u0131 k\u00f6k h\u00fccre tedavileri uygulanabilir. Etkileri s\u0131n\u0131rl\u0131d\u0131r olsa da do\u011fru hasta grubunda olduk\u00e7a memnuniyet sa\u011flayan tedavilerdir.\n\nKal\u00e7a Protezi \u00d6ncesi Haz\u0131rl\u0131k S\u00fcreci\nKal\u00e7a protezi ameliyat\u0131 da di\u011fer bir \u00e7ok ortopedi ameliyat\u0131 gibi operasyon \u00f6ncesi en az 8 saatlik a\u00e7l\u0131k gerektiren bir operasyondur. Hastaya \u00f6nce anestezi muayenesi yap\u0131larak hastan\u0131n anestezi almas\u0131nda herhangi bir risk olup olmad\u0131\u011f\u0131 \u00f6\u011frenilir devam\u0131nda rutin kan tahlilleri yap\u0131l\u0131r, hasta i\u00e7in kan temin edilir, hastan\u0131n kal\u00e7a eklemine uygun kal\u00e7a protez \u00fcr\u00fcn\u00fc temin edilir ve ihtiya\u00e7 dahilinde di\u011fer It is situated at around 1,350 meters above sea level on the western slopes of Mount Hermon, southeast of Beirut near the Syrian border, and approximately halfway between Jezzine and Damascus. T\u00fcm organlar\u0131 ve dokular\u0131 olu\u015fturan ana h\u00fccrelerdir. D\u00f6llenmi\u015f bir yumurta ile ba\u015flad\u0131\u011f\u0131m\u0131z hayat yolculu\u011fumuzda \u015fimdiki fiziki yap\u0131m\u0131za ula\u015fmam\u0131za kadarki t\u00fcm s\u00fcreci k\u00f6k h\u00fccrelerimiz yapar.\n\nKan, kemik, k\u0131k\u0131rdak, kas, ba\u011f, di\u015f, sa\u00e7, cilt gibi dokular\u0131m\u0131z\u0131n olu\u015fmas\u0131n\u0131, b\u00fcy\u00fcmesini, geli\u015fmesi sa\u011flayan h\u00fccrelerimizdir. Ya\u011flar\u0131m\u0131zdan haz\u0131rlanan k\u00f6k h\u00fccrelerimiz kullan\u0131m alan\u0131 en geni\u015f olan h\u00fccrelerdir. Sa\u00e7 tedavileri, cilt tedavileri, omurga disk tedavileri, kas tedavileri, ba\u011f ve tendon tedavileri, k\u0131k\u0131rdak tedavileri, kemik tedavileri gibi hem estetik hem de ortopedinin t\u00fcm tedavilerinde kullan\u0131ma uygundur.\n\nKemik ili\u011fi k\u00f6k h\u00fccre: Kemik ili\u011fi h\u00fccrelerimiz v\u00fccudumuzdaki b\u00fcy\u00fck kemiklerimizin i\u00e7inde yo\u011fun olarak bulunur. Bu s\u00fcre k\u00f6k h\u00fccrenin al\u0131m\u0131 esnas\u0131nda ac\u0131 duymaman\u0131z i\u00e7indir. K\u00f6k h\u00fccre tedavi i\u00e7in haz\u0131rlan\u0131rken ve uygulama esnas\u0131nda anestezi alt\u0131nda olman\u0131z zorunlu de\u011fildir. \u0130\u015flemden sonra hastane odas\u0131nda yakla\u015f\u0131k 3 \u2013 4 dinlenerek taburcu olabilirsiniz.\n\nK\u00f6k h\u00fccre tedavileri hasta konforu a\u00e7\u0131s\u0131ndan olduk\u00e7a caziptir ve uyguland\u0131\u011f\u0131 b\u00f6lgede 6 ay boyunca doku iyile\u015fmesi sa\u011flar.\nK\u00f6k H\u00fccre Dizde Hangi Tedavilerde Kullan\u0131l\u0131r?\n\nK\u00f6k h\u00fccre ile Menisk\u00fcs Tedavisi: Menisk\u00fcs y\u0131rt\u0131klar\u0131 ve dejenerasyonlar\u0131nda grade II seviyesine kadar k\u00f6k h\u00fccre tedavileri kullan\u0131labilir. Grade III ve \u00fczeri menisk\u00fcs hasarlar\u0131nda ise cerrahi tedaviler uygulan\u0131p ameliyat sonras\u0131 k\u00f6k h\u00fccre tedavileri h\u0131zl\u0131 doku iyile\u015fmesi i\u00e7in yard\u0131mc\u0131 tedavi olarak kullan\u0131labilir.\nK\u00f6k h\u00fccre ile K\u0131k\u0131rdak Tedavisi: Diz ekleminde k\u0131k\u0131rdak incelmesi, k\u0131k\u0131rdak azalmas\u0131 ve k\u0131k\u0131rdak hasarlar\u0131nda k\u00f6k h\u00fccre tedavisi ile k\u0131k\u0131rda dokusunda art\u0131\u015f, hasarl\u0131 dokunun onar\u0131m\u0131 i\u00e7in etkili bir tedavidir. Sa\u00e7 tedavileri, cilt tedavileri, omurga disk tedavileri, kas tedavileri, ba\u011f ve tendon tedavileri, k\u0131k\u0131rdak tedavileri, kemik tedavileri gibi hem estetik hem de ortopedinin t\u00fcm tedavilerinde kullan\u0131ma uygundur.\n\nKemik ili\u011fi k\u00f6k h\u00fccre: Kemik ili\u011fi h\u00fccrelerimiz v\u00fccudumuzdaki b\u00fcy\u00fck kemiklerimizin i\u00e7inde yo\u011fun olarak bulunur. Al\u0131nan k\u00f6k h\u00fccre a\u00e7\u0131s\u0131ndan zengin kemik ili\u011fi \u00f6zel santrif\u00fcj cihaz\u0131 ve k\u00f6k h\u00fccre biyolo\u011fu taraf\u0131ndan yakla\u015f\u0131k 30 dk santrif\u00fcj a\u015famalar\u0131ndan ge\u00e7irilerek tedavide kullan\u0131labilir hale getirilir ve hedef b\u00f6lgeye (Kal\u00e7a eklemi, diz eklemi, ayak eklemi vs) tedavi uygulan\u0131r.\n\nYa\u011fdan mezenkimal k\u00f6k h\u00fccre haz\u0131rlan\u0131\u015f\u0131 i\u00e7in ameliyathane \u015fartlar\u0131nda genel anestezi alt\u0131nda g\u00f6bek b\u00f6lgesinden mini liposuction ile 100- 150 cc k\u00f6k h\u00fccre a\u00e7\u0131s\u0131ndan zengin ya\u011f dokusu liposuctin kanulleri ile al\u0131n\u0131r. Al\u0131nan k\u00f6k h\u00fccre a\u00e7\u0131s\u0131ndan zengin ya\u011f dokusu \u00f6zel santrif\u00fcj cihaz\u0131 ve k\u00f6k h\u00fccre biyolo\u011fu taraf\u0131ndan yakla\u015f\u0131k 60 dk santrif\u00fcj a\u015famalar\u0131ndan ge\u00e7irilerek tedavide kullan\u0131labilir hale getirilir ve hedef b\u00f6lgeye (kal\u00e7a eklemi, diz eklemi, ayak eklemi, omuz, dirsek vs) tedavi uygulan\u0131r.\n\nK\u00f6k h\u00fccre tedavisi i\u00e7in k\u0131smi s\u00fcreli bir anestezi alman\u0131z yeterlidir. Bu s\u00fcre k\u00f6k h\u00fccrenin al\u0131m\u0131 esnas\u0131nda ac\u0131 duymaman\u0131z i\u00e7indir. K\u00f6k h\u00fccre tedavi i\u00e7in haz\u0131rlan\u0131rken ve uygulama esnas\u0131nda anestezi alt\u0131nda olman\u0131z zorunlu de\u011fildir. \u0130\u015flemden sonra hastane odas\u0131nda yakla\u015f\u0131k 3 \u2013 4 dinlenerek taburcu olabilirsiniz.\n\nK\u00f6k h\u00fccre tedavileri hasta konforu a\u00e7\u0131s\u0131ndan olduk\u00e7a caziptir ve uyguland\u0131\u011f\u0131 b\u00f6lgede 6 ay boyunca doku iyile\u015fmesi sa\u011flar.\nK\u00f6k H\u00fccre Dizde Hangi Tedavilerde Kullan\u0131l\u0131r?\n\nK\u00f6k h\u00fccre ile Menisk\u00fcs Tedavisi: Menisk\u00fcs y\u0131rt\u0131klar\u0131 ve dejenerasyonlar\u0131nda grade II seviyesine kadar k\u00f6k h\u00fccre tedavileri kullan\u0131labilir. Grade III ve \u00fczeri menisk\u00fcs hasarlar\u0131nda ise cerrahi tedaviler uygulan\u0131p ameliyat sonras\u0131 k\u00f6k h\u00fccre tedavileri h\u0131zl\u0131 doku iyile\u015fmesi i\u00e7in yard\u0131mc\u0131 tedavi olarak kullan\u0131labilir.\nK\u00f6k h\u00fccre ile K\u0131k\u0131rdak Tedavisi: Diz ekleminde k\u0131k\u0131rdak incelmesi, k\u0131k\u0131rdak azalmas\u0131 ve k\u0131k\u0131rdak hasarlar\u0131nda k\u00f6k h\u00fccre tedavisi ile k\u0131k\u0131rda dokusunda art\u0131\u015f, hasarl\u0131 dokunun onar\u0131m\u0131 i\u00e7in etkili bir tedavidir. Travma sonucu olu\u015fan hasarlarda ciddi k\u0131k\u0131rdak hasarlar\u0131nda ise cerrahi operasyondan sonra daha h\u0131zl\u0131 doku iyile\u015fmesi i\u00e7in kullan\u0131lmas\u0131 \u00e7ok \u00f6nemlidir.\nK\u00f6k h\u00fccre ile Ba\u011f Tedavisi: Diz kapa\u011f\u0131 ba\u011flar\u0131, \u00d6n \u00e7apraz ba\u011f, arka \u00e7apraz ba\u011f, i\u00e7 yan ba\u011f, d\u0131\u015f yan ba\u011f y\u0131rt\u0131klar\u0131 ve dejenerasyonlar\u0131nda grade II seviyesine kadar k\u00f6k h\u00fccre tedavileri kullan\u0131labilir. k\u0131sm\u0131n\u0131n disk dokusunun omurlardan ayr\u0131ld\u0131\u011f\u0131nda bel kaslar\u0131 ve bel sinirleri bu durumdan olumsuz etkilenirler.\n\nBel f\u0131t\u0131\u011f\u0131nda belin
